 (in) likewise (manner), moreover, nay...neither, one, then(-refore), though, what, with, yea.","pos":"adverb","usage":"also(5x), as(3x), even(2x), again(1x), and(1x)"},"H1572":{"id":"H1572","lemma":"גָּמָא","translit":"gâmâʼ","pron":"gaw-maw'","derivation":"a primitive root (literally or figuratively) to absorb","strongs_def":"to absorb","kjv_def":"swallow, drink.","pos":"verb","usage":"swallow(1x), drink(1x)"},"H1573":{"id":"H1573","lemma":"גֹּמֶא","translit":"gômeʼ","pron":"go'-meh","derivation":"from H1572 (גָּמָא);","strongs_def":"properly, an absorbent, i.e. the bulrush (from its porosity); specifically the papyrus","kjv_def":"(bul-) rush.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"rush(2x), bulrush(2x)"},"H1574":{"id":"H1574","lemma":"גֹּמֶד","translit":"gômed","pron":"go'-med","derivation":"from an unused root apparently meaning to grasp;","strongs_def":"properly, a span","kjv_def":"cubit.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"cubit(1x)"},"H1575":{"id":"H1575","lemma":"גַּמָּד","translit":"gammâd","pron":"gam-mawd'","derivation":"from the same as H1574 (גֹּמֶד);","strongs_def":"a warrior (as grasping weapons)","kjv_def":"Gammadims.","pos":"masculine plural noun","usage":"Gammadims(1x)"},"H1576":{"id":"H1576","lemma":"גְּמוּל","translit":"gᵉmûwl","pron":"ghem-ool'","derivation":"from H1580 (גָּמַל);","strongs_def":"treatment, i.e. an act (of good or ill); by implication, service or requital","kjv_def":"[phrase] as hast served, benefit, desert, deserving, that which he hath given, recompense, reward.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"recompense(10x), reward(3x), benefit(2x), given(1x), deserve(1x)"},"H1577":{"id":"H1577","lemma":"גָּמוּל","translit":"gâmûwl","pron":"gaw-mool'","derivation":"passive participle of H1580 (גָּמַל); rewarded;","strongs_def":"Gamul, an Israelite","kjv_def":"Gamul. See also H1014 (בֵּית גָּמוּל)."},"H1578":{"id":"H1578","lemma":"גְּמוּלָה","translit":"gᵉmûwlâh","pron":"ghem-oo-law'","derivation":"feminine of H1576 (גְּמוּל);","strongs_def":"meaning the same","kjv_def":"deed, recompense, such a reward.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"recompence(1x), deed(1x), reward(1x)"},"H1579":{"id":"H1579","lemma":"גִּמְזוֹ","translit":"Gimzôw","pron":"ghim-zo'","derivation":"of uncertain derivation;","strongs_def":"Gimzo, a place in Palestine","kjv_def":"Gimzo."},"H1580":{"id":"H1580","lemma":"גָּמַל","translit":"gâmal","pron":"gaw-mal'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"to treat a person (well or ill), i.e. benefit or requite; by implication (of toil), to ripen, i.e. (specifically) to wean","kjv_def":"bestow on, deal bountifully, do (good), recompense, requite, reward, ripen, [phrase] serve, mean, yield.","pos":"verb","usage":"wean(10x), reward(8x), do(4x), bestowed(2x), recompense(2x), requite(1x), ripening(1x), served(1x), yielded(1x)"},"H1581":{"id":"H1581","lemma":"גָּמָל","translit":"gâmâl","pron":"gaw-mawl'","derivation":"apparently from H1580 (גָּמַל) (in the sense of labor or burden-bearing);","strongs_def":"a camel","kjv_def":"camel.","pos":"masculine/feminine noun","usage":"camel(54x)"},"H1582":{"id":"H1582","lemma":"גְּמַלִּי","translit":"Gᵉmallîy","pron":"ghem-al-lee'","derivation":"probably from H1581 (גָּמָל); cameldriver;","strongs_def":"Gemalli, an Israelite","kjv_def":"Gemalli."},"H1583":{"id":"H1583","lemma":"גַּמְלִיאֵל","translit":"Gamlîyʼêl","pron":"gam-lee-ale'","derivation":"from H1580 (גָּמַל) and H410 (אֵל); reward of God;","strongs_def":"Gamliel, an Israelite","kjv_def":"Gamaliel.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Gamaliel(5x)"},"H1584":{"id":"H1584","lemma":"גָּמַר","translit":"gâmar","pron":"gaw-mar'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"to end (in the sense of completion or failure)","kjv_def":"cease, come to an end, fail, perfect, perform.","pos":"verb","usage":"cease(1x), fail(1x), perfect(1x), perform(1x)"},"H1585":{"id":"H1585","lemma":"גְּמַר","translit":"gᵉmar","pron":"ghem-ar'","derivation":"(Aramaic) corresponding to H1584 (גָּמַר)","strongs_def":"{to end (in the sense of completion or failure)}","kjv_def":"perfect.","pos":"verb","usage":"perfect(1x)"},"H1586":{"id":"H1586","lemma":"גֹּמֶר","translit":"Gômer","pron":"go'-mer","derivation":"from H1584 (גָּמַר); completion;","strongs_def":"Gomer, the name of a son of Japheth and of his descendants; also of a Hebrewess","kjv_def":"Gomer.","pos":"proper feminine noun, proper masculine noun","usage":"Gomer(6x)"},"H1587":{"id":"H1587","lemma":"גְּמַרְיָה","translit":"Gᵉmaryâh","pron":"ghem-ar-yaw'","derivation":"or גְּמַרְיָהוּ; from H1584 (גָּמַר) and H3050 (יָהּ); Jah has perfected;","strongs_def":"Gemarjah, the name of two Israelites","kjv_def":"Gemariah.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Gemariah(5x)"},"H1588":{"id":"H1588","lemma":"גַּן","translit":"gan","pron":"gan","derivation":"from H1598 (גָּנַן);","strongs_def":"a garden (as fenced)","kjv_def":"garden.","pos":"masculine/feminine noun, proper locative noun","usage":"garden(42x)"},"H1589":{"id":"H1589","lemma":"גָּנַב","translit":"gânab","pron":"gaw-nab'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"to thieve (literally or figuratively); by implication, to deceive","kjv_def":"carry away, [idiom] indeed, secretly bring, steal (away), get by stealth.","pos":"verb","usage":"steal(30x), brought(1x)"},"H1590":{"id":"H1590","lemma":"גַּנָּב","translit":"gannâb","pron":"gaw-nab'","derivation":"from H1589 (גָּנַב);","strongs_def":"a stealer","kjv_def":"thief.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"thief(17x)"},"H1591":{"id":"H1591","lemma":"גְּנֵבָה","translit":"gᵉnêbâh","pron":"ghen-ay-baw'","derivation":"from H1589 (גָּנַב);","strongs_def":"stealing, i.e. (concretely) something stolen","kjv_def":"theft.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"theft(2x)"},"H1592":{"id":"H1592","lemma":"גְּנֻבַת","translit":"Gᵉnubath","pron":"ghen-oo-bath'","derivation":"from H1589 (גָּנַב); theft;","strongs_def":"Genubath, an Edomitish prince","kjv_def":"Genubath."},"H1593":{"id":"H1593","lemma":"גַּנָּה","translit":"gannâh","pron":"gan-naw'","derivation":"feminine of H1588 (גַּן);","strongs_def":"a garden","kjv_def":"garden.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"garden(12x)"},"H1594":{"id":"H1594","lemma":"גִּנָּה","translit":"ginnâh","pron":"ghin-naw'","derivation":"another form for H1593 (גַּנָּה)","strongs_def":"{a garden}","kjv_def":"garden.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"garden(4x)"},"H1595":{"id":"H1595","lemma":"גֶּנֶז","translit":"genez","pron":"gheh'-nez","derivation":"from an unused root meaning to store;","strongs_def":"treasure; by implication, a coffer","kjv_def":"chest, treasury.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"treasury(2x), chest(1x)"},"H1596":{"id":"H1596","lemma":"גְּנַז","translit":"gᵉnaz","pron":"ghen-az'","derivation":"(Aramaic) corresponding to H1595 (גֶּנֶז);","strongs_def":"treasure","kjv_def":"treasure.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"treasure(3x)"},"H1597":{"id":"H1597","lemma":"גִּנְזַךְ","translit":"ginzak","pron":"ghin-zak'","derivation":"prolonged from H1595 (גֶּנֶז);","strongs_def":"a treasury","kjv_def":"treasury."},"H1598":{"id":"H1598","lemma":"גָּנַן","translit":"gânan","pron":"gaw-nan'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"to hedge about, i.e. (generally) protect","kjv_def":"defend.","pos":"verb","usage":"defend(8x)"},"H1599":{"id":"H1599","lemma":"גִּנְּתוֹן","translit":"Ginnᵉthôwn","pron":"ghin-neth-one","derivation":"or גִּנְּתוֹ; from H1598 (גָּנַן); gardener;","strongs_def":"Ginnethon or Ginnetho, an Israelite","kjv_def":"Ginnetho, Ginnethon.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Ginnethon(2x), Ginnetho(1x)"}}